---
id: com.example.fixture.pkg-b
name: PkgB
version: 0.1.0
extends: [com.example.fixture.pkg-a@1.0.0]
---

Fixture package: declares the `TaskCard` React component, which renders
a `Task` (from `@fixture/pkg-a`) and subscribes to its updates via
`useObject` from `@dxos/echo-react`.

## Extensions

| Term        | URI                            |
| ----------- | ------------------------------ |
| `component` | `org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0`   |

## Components

```mdl
component TaskCard
  desc: |
    Card-style renderer for a Task. Subscribes to the object via useObject so
    changes (title, description, done) re-render automatically. The `done`
    checkbox calls the update callback to toggle state in place.
  props:
    task: Task                         # echo-type from pkg-a (Task.Task at the call site)
  uses:
    useObject from @dxos/echo-react    # subscribe to Task and obtain a mutating update callback
  note: |
    No outbound events — done toggle is handled by mutating the ECHO object in
    place via update(draft => { draft.done = ... }). Replication / persistence
    is handled by ECHO downstream of the component.
  layout: |
    <article>
      <h3>{title}</h3>
      [{description?}]
      <label><input type=checkbox checked={done} /> done</label>
    </article>
```

